Chef and His Apps

Chef's phone has a total storage capacity of S MB.

He already has 2 apps installed on his phone:

The first app occupies X MB
The second app occupies Y MB

Chef wants to install a third app which requires Z MB of storage.

However, if there is not enough free space, Chef may need to delete one or both of the existing apps.

❓ Task

For each test case, determine the minimum number of apps Chef needs to delete so that there is enough space to install the new app.

📥 Input Format
The first line contains an integer T — number of test cases.
Each test case contains four integers:
S → total storage capacity
X → space used by first app
Y → space used by second app
Z → space required for new app
📤 Output Format

For each test case, print a single integer:

0 → if no app needs to be deleted
1 → if deleting one app is enough
2 → if both apps must be deleted


import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;

class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int t = sc.nextInt();
		
		while(t-->0){
		    int s = sc.nextInt();
		    int x = sc.nextInt();
		    int y = sc.nextInt();
		    int z = sc.nextInt();
		    
		    if(x+y+z<=s) System.out.println(0);
		    else if(x+z<=s || y+z<=s) System.out.println(1);
		    else System.out.println(2);
		}

	}
}
